As no code is provided in the question i am guessing that you are not calling GET after PUT is finished.

If you write

    PUT CALL
    GET CALL

It will never work. If you write

    PUT CALL
    setTimeout(() =&gt; {
        GET CALL
    }, 200);

It is not guaranteed that you will get updated data. Correct way of calling would be

    PUT CALL.subscribe(() =&gt; {
        GET CALL
    });

It guaranties that GET will be called after PUT is finished.

