You could easily create multiple [HOC][1] where each would represent one of your layout components. Then you&#39;d just wrap component you want with desired layout:

    const withMainLayout = (Component) =&gt; (props) =&gt; {
        return (
            &lt;MainLayout&gt;
                &lt;Component {...props} /&gt;
            &lt;/MainLayout&gt;
        )
    }

And then you would use it like

    const LayoutDashboard = withMainLayout(DashboardComponent);


  [1]: https://reactjs.org/docs/higher-order-components.html

This way you can create X layout and corresponding HOC&#39;s and then just wrap desired components.

