Type aliases do not support inheritance. You can do something similar using intersection types:

```ts
export type A = B &amp; { a: number, b: string };

export type B = {
    c: string
};
```
[Play](https://www.typescriptlang.org/play/#code/KYDwDg9gTgLgBDAnmYcCCcC8cBCcBkcA3nAIYBccAdgK4C2ARsFADRwOUDKMUAllQHM4AXwDcAKHGhIsBMlR5sRcXFVwAxpQDOPfgPFigA)

Or you can use interfaces (in this case it really does not matter if these types are type aliases or interfaces): 

```ts
export interface A extends B { a: number, b: string };

export interface B {
    c: string
};
```
[play](https://www.typescriptlang.org/play/#code/KYDwDg9gTgLgBASwHY2FAZgQwMbDgQTlFSQBMBnOAITgG85MAuOJAVwFsAjNAGjk+bkYUZAHM4AXwDcAKBmhIsRCjRZc1OjLja42QcLEzpQA)

